(1) The Railways shall not declare or take part in a lock-out or in the continuation of a lock-out, and no employee or registered or statutory trade union or other person shall declare or take part in a strike or the continuation of a strike until the conditions which are specified in sub-paragraph (2) and which are applicable to the occasion have been fulfilled.
